41KRB5_LIB_FUNCTION krb5_error_code KRB5_LIB_CALL
42_krb5_s4u2self_to_checksumdata(krb5_context context,
43 const PA_S4U2Self *self,
44 krb5_data *data)
45{
46 krb5_error_code ret;
47 krb5_ssize_t ssize;
48 krb5_storage *sp;
49 size_t size;
50 size_t i;
51
52 sp = krb5_storage_emem();
53 if (sp == NULL)
54 return krb5_enomem(context);
55 krb5_storage_set_flags(sp, KRB5_STORAGE_BYTEORDER_LE);
56 ret = krb5_store_int32(sp, self->name.name_type);
57 if (ret) {
58 krb5_clear_error_message(context);
59 return ret;
60 }
61 for (i = 0; i < self->name.name_string.len; i++) {
62 size = strlen(self->name.name_string.val[i]);
63 ssize = krb5_storage_write(sp, self->name.name_string.val[i], size);
64 if (ssize != (krb5_ssize_t)size)
65 return krb5_enomem(context);
66 }
67 size = strlen(self->realm);
68 ssize = krb5_storage_write(sp, self->realm, size);
69 if (ssize != (krb5_ssize_t)size)
70 return krb5_enomem(context);
71 size = strlen(self->auth);
72 ssize = krb5_storage_write(sp, self->auth, size);
73 if (ssize != (krb5_ssize_t)size)
74 return krb5_enomem(context);
75
76 ret = krb5_storage_to_data(sp, data);
77 krb5_storage_free(sp);
78 return ret;
79}

81KRB5_LIB_FUNCTION void KRB5_LIB_CALL
82_krb5_debug_backtrace(krb5_context context)
83{
84#if defined(HAVE_BACKTRACE) && defined(HAVE_BACKTRACE_SYMBOLS) && !defined(HEIMDAL_SMALLER)
85 void *stack[128];
86 char **strs = NULL;
87 int i, frames = backtrace(stack, sizeof(stack) / sizeof(stack[0]));
88 if (frames > 0)
89 strs = backtrace_symbols(stack, frames);
90 if (strs) {
91 for (i = 0; i < frames; i++)
92 _krb5_debug(context, 10, "frame %d: %s", i, strs[i]);
93 free(strs);
94 }
95#endif
96}
97
98KRB5_LIB_FUNCTION krb5_error_code KRB5_LIB_CALL
99_krb5_einval(krb5_context context, const char *func, unsigned long argn)
100{
101#ifndef HEIMDAL_SMALLER
102 krb5_set_error_message(context, EINVAL,
103 N_("programmer error: invalid argument to %s argument %lu",
104 "function:line"),
105 func, argn);
106 if (_krb5_have_debug(context, 10)) {
107 _krb5_debug(context, 10, "invalid argument to function %s argument %lu",
108 func, argn);
109 _krb5_debug_backtrace(context);
110 }
111#endif
112 return EINVAL;
113}
